text = "[b]Overview[/b]
You begin with a [i]NAND[/i] or an [i]AND[/i] and a [i]NOT[/i] and you will always have the following Chips: an [i]Input[/i], an [i]Output[/i] and a [i]Seven Segment Display[/i]

[b]Input and Outputs[/b]
To add an Input or an Output to your Circuit, you need to add the [i]Input[/i] or the [i]Output[/i] block to your Circuit

[b]Chips[/b]
To add a Chip to your Circuit, you click on to the button of the Chip in the top bar or select the chip in the Chip Library and press [i]Add[/i].
To remove a chip from your Circuit, you select the chip and press [i]Delete[/i] on your keyboard.
To delete a chip from your Project, you select the chip in the chip library and press [i]Delete[/i].

[b]Wires[/b]
To add a wire, you click and hold the pin you want to connect from ( must be on the right side ) and connect it to the pin you want to connect to.
To remove a wire, you click and hold the pin, you want to disconnect ( must be on the left side of the chip ) and move the wire into empty space."
